cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.AI. 

The paper focuses on image retrieval using deep neural networks and hashing techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel method for simultaneous feature representation and hash function learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of rank correlation space and attention models, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach to capture the local spatial and global semantic nature of images, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
